cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.COMM, cs.LG 

This paper discusses multiple access techniques for downlink communication systems, which are typically studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), communication (cs.COMM), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new technique called rate splitting multiple access, which aims to generalize and outperform existing techniques such as SDMA and NOMA. Therefore, it is likely to be relevant to researchers in these sub-categories.
